LABORATORY
Reviewed available outside records including his April 8, 2008, operative note and his PET reports.  I have requested CT reports.  His films are all on QREADS.
IMPRESSION/REPORT/PLAN
#1 Biopsy-proven recurrent/residual rectal cancer
Mr. Kraatz presents for an opinion regarding management of rectal cancer.  This was incompletely resected April 8, 2008, and now he is referred for consideration of surgical resection and intra-operative radiation therapy.  I discussed the factors that enter into this decision, and at this time we will restage the patient with a CT chest, abdomen, and pelvis and PET scan, and this should be compared to his prior films which are on QREADS.  Patient will then meet with Dr. Sukey Orcutt from Colon and Rectal Surgery for a formal surgical visit.  Dr. Borrero will see him afterward for a radiation oncology perspective if he is surgically resectable.  Patient will also meet with Medical Oncology for chemotherapy recommendations.  If surgery is undertaken, then he will need to meet with Thrombophilia Clinic for discontinuation of his Coumadin in what will likely include heparin management.  He will also meet with Stomal Therapy given the peristomal irritation.  Discussed in detail with the patient and answered questions.
#2 Preoperative medical evaluation
An ECG will be checked in conjunction with his lab studies.  If the ECG is abnormal, he would require cardiology consultation prior to surgical resection.  However, we will hold off on ordering this pending Dr. Harvey evaluation.
Discussed with Dr. Ashley Haley, note to follow.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: Yes, not on file at Hallberg Family Practice Community Hospital.

